items.name: Lansley - Hentai University
items.description:
This is a LoRA for the character Lansley, from Hentai University a game by Noodle Jacuzzi.

Lansley's art is from the artist Oreteki18kin, the set -

Haramitai! Natsu Nakadashi Kyouka Gasshuku

I've been working my way through making these for all the characters currently in the game, and sharing them in the Discord for HU, but figured I should also put them up here.

In general, I'm working from pretty limited image sets, so expect the results to be a bit wonky at times. These (and the rest of the gym girls) especially only have about 15 images to work from each, and they're not ideal images. It still works, but it takes more finagling that some of the other characters for sure.

I recommend a weight of around 0.5, possibly lower depending if you're combining the character LoRA with other styles/costumes/etc. along with tagging some defining characteristics of the character you're generating. Higher than that can really push the artist's original style, and may cause you issues.

All characters I train have a "character tag" added into the set to help generate them fairly reliably.

Recommended LoRA Weight - 0.5 for fairly flexible, higher if you want more of the original artist's style, lower if it doesn't play nice with other loras.

Character tag - HULansley
Recommended tags - pink hair, medium breasts, ponytail, brown eyes, hair pulled back, hair slicked back,

I may have forgotten to check and tag eye color when doing my testing, but hey. If you want it to be "set accurate" be sure to tag.

I've got quite a backlog of these made up already, so I'll be uploading them on and off.

Check my other uploads as I put them out for more HU characters, and if you want any specific character put up soon, let me know.

items.name: 【Art Style】Yoongonji Style
items.description:
Introduction

A LoRA model trained with images illustrated by Yoongonji. The trigger tag is 'yoongnoji'. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.6 version (original) YesMix.

Due to the use of dropout during training to reduce overfitting and enhance generalization ability, the generated results may not be too similar to the original images.

Cautions (Must Read)

For anime model,

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

  • Some preview images are generated using 'Hires Fix' and upscaled using 'SD Upscale'. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

BTW, make sure set this option in 'Stable Diffusion' settings to 'CPU' to successfully regenerate the preview images with the same seed.

  • The training resolution of this model is 1024x1024, so generating resolution must not exceed this range. Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: Gothic Doll
items.description:
This is a LoHa learned in Replicant-V3.0.

To use it, you need a model of Stable Diffusion V2.1-768 series and LyCORIS installed.

(When run on SD1 series models, the following error occurs.

RuntimeError: The size of tensor a (768) must match the size of tensor b (1024) at non-singleton dimension 1).

The file should be placed under the models/LyCORIS folder.

This is created to output a male doll with a gothic feel.

The effect is too strong and may be best used at -0.5 to 0.5.

As a side effect of this LoHa, applying a positive value will increase the realism, and applying a negative value will make more animation style.

The training process uses about 300 images generated by niji journey and about 100 images generated by Replicant v3.

The license is taken over from Replicant v3.

license : https://freedevproject.org/faipl-1.0-sd/

-------------------------------------------------------------------

これはReplicant-V3.0 で学習した‎LoHaです。

使用にはStable Diffusion V2.1-768 系のモデルとLyCORISのインストールが必要です。

(SD1系のモデルで実行すると、以下のようなエラーが出ます。

RuntimeError: テンソル a (768) のサイズは、非シングルトン次元 1 でのテンソル b (1024) のサイズと一致する必要があります。)

ファイルは models\LyCORIS フォルダの配下に配置してください。

ゴシックな雰囲気の男性ドールを出力するLoHaを目指しました。

効果が強いので、-0.5～0.5程度で使用するのが良いかもしれません。

このLoHaは副次効果として、プラス適用するとリアルさが増し、マイナス適用するとアニメ調になります。

学習過程では、niji journeyで生成した画像約300枚と、Replicant v3で生成した画像約100枚を使用しています。

ライセンスはReplicant v3に準じます。

ライセンス: https://freedevproject.org/faipl-1.0-sd/

items.name: Métal Hurlant Comics - Moebius, Bilal, Druillet
items.description:
Métal Hurlant (literal translation: "Howling Metal," "Screaming Metal") is a French comics anthology of science fiction and horror comics stories. Originally created in 1974, the anthologies ceased publication in 1987 but revived between 2002 and 2004 in multilingual editions, and then again in 2020.

Update 17/07/23: There will not be another version released for 1.5, all my focus will be dedicated to SDXL. I will train a better version there, with a bigger dataset, higher resolutions, and comprehensive captioning.

⚠️ CAUTION - Alpha Release⚠️

This version is experimental. It can handle portraits quite well but struggles with elaborate compositions containing multiple subjects. I'm working on a more complete version but I felt it was already able to output some good images, so still worth sharing if you're interested.

💥Showcase images 💥

Please note that the showcase images have been upscaled with Multidiffusion (adds sharpness) and lightly edited with Lightroom (enhances colours). You should still be able to get a resembling result by using the prompts provided, but it will not be of the same quality.

How to use

  • Tested at weight 1: <lora:methurlant:1>

  • The trigger word is methurlant, additional words are intricate, atmospheric, surreal, gritty, cinematic, stylized, contrast, comics, eerie, cybernetic, futuristic, dystopian, etc.

  • The resolution should be 512x512 or higher

  • The best checkpoints are the creative ones (Deliberate, Lyriel, Dreamshaper, etc.)

  • Works ok with realistic checkpoints (CyberRealistic, ConsistentFactor, RealisticVision, etc.)

  • Does not work well with Anime checkpoints (AbyssOrangeMix, Anything, etc.)

  • Good prompting is needed, please see the trigger words and the showcase images

  • Works better with a colorful VAE

Dataset

  • A total of 100 images from various Métal Hurlant artists: Bilal, Druillet, Moebius, etc.

  • All images were curated to remove comics aspects and focus on the art only, with no text, no panels, no speech bubbles

  • Provides a generic French blend without too much emphasis on any artist

  • 0 caption

  • Clip Skip 1 training

Suzhou embroidery is one of the four famous embroideries in China, originating from Suzhou and its surrounding areas in Jiangsu province. Suzhou embroidery is characterized by bright colors, fine stitches, realistic patterns, and a sense of three-dimensionality and depth. Suzhou embroidery’s techniques include flat stitch, random stitch, hidden stitch, knotting, inlaying and other methods, which can create different textures and effects. Suzhou embroidery has a wide range of themes, such as flowers and birds, figures, landscapes, animals and so on. It has both traditional classic patterns and modern innovative designs. Suzhou embroidery is a treasure of Chinese traditional culture and a masterpiece of world art.

This model has a small training dataset and is only for testing purposes, so it cannot fully show the charm of Suzhou embroidery.

⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻⸻

items.name: Delorean-80s-aerobics
items.description:
And here we have another LoRA from the Delorean series. This time...

1980's aerobics! Trashy, rad, ugly pictures of poor quality like cut out from an 80's magazine.

See the version description. It describes the changes from versions 1 and 2. The main difference is that LoRA works better with cfg<7 (4 is the optimum).

Also... If you like my work, I'd be glad if you would tip it with a small amount to help me partially cover my expenses with Google Colab. Thanks a lot! https://ko-fi.com/stepaan

How to:

Lora is trained on period pictures from sports and fashion magazines. I certainly didn't want to enhance them in any way (OK, I did enhance them, but only enough to emphasize the main point). My goal was to capture the style of the photos as much as possible. So don't expect crystal clear pictures! On the contrary, they will be full of noise, scratches and with strange colors.

So... :

  • I recommend the cleanest checkpoint possible. Stylized models aren't retro enough ;-). As always, analogMadness is the obvious choice. (From v3.0 it's possible to use the checkpoint of your choice. Still applies, you might get images, that are far from the 80's.)

  • Anyone who doesn't like strong stylization and low quality (understand retro) results can reduce the strength to taste (0.5-0.7), but once again, LoRA is supposed to work at full strength (1.0). If you get low quality images, go find a better checkpoint. ;-)

  • LoRA knows quite a few types of aerobic clothing. That's why I recommend using Cutoff Regions (I use ComfyUI, I hope that's what it's called in A1111).

  • I recommend dpmppsde karras. Or use the sampler that suits your imagination. Also this VAE https://civitai.com/models/88390/difconsistency-raw-vae-pack helps to achieve more desaturated retro feel.

  • HighResFix is a must, Face Restore is a no no!

Sample prompt:

See images. The Lora can produce huge variety of images (quality wise, retro-ness wise).

Enjoy the atmosphere of sweaty gyms from 40 years ago. More Deloreans coming soon ;-)
